          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The detection  process permits the measurement of the",
                " photoneutron  multiplicity  I  and   therefore   the",
                " simultaneous  and  independent  measurement  of each",
                " partial inclusive photoneutron cross  section  SIG-i",
                " for each value of Eg-i. The total photoneutron cross",
                " section SIG was obtained as a sum of the sig-i."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The inclusive  partial  photoneutron  cross  sections",
                " sig(g,1n),  sig(g,2n),  and the  total  photoneutron",
                " cross  section  sig(g,n-tot),  which is equal to the",
                " sum of the partial ones, for O-16 have been measured",
                " with  monoenergetic  photons  in  the  energy region",
                " above  the  giant  resonance  and  below  the  meson",
                " thresholds.  Comparison  with  other  data shows the",
                " dominance of  the  (g,pn)  process  in  this  energy",
                " region  and  thus  underscores the importance of the",
                " mechanism  of  photon  absorption  by  a  correlated",
                " proton-neutron pair in nucleus;  thus,  satisfactory",
                " agreement of modern versions  of  the  quasideuteron",
                " theory with the data has been obtained. The measured",
                " integrated total photoneutron cross  section  up  to",
                " 140  MeV is 0.67 (0.07) TRK sum-rule units.  Because",
                " the  low  thresholds  the  following  reactions  can",
                " participate:  (g,n+p) - 23 MeV, (g,n+2p) - 30.5 MeV,",
                " (g,n+a) - 25.9 MeV,  (g,n+p+a) - 34.6 MeV in  (g,1n)",
                " reaction  cross  sections  and  (g,2n+p) - 33.5 mev,",
                " (g,2n+2p)  -  35.5   MeV,   (g,2n+a)   -   39   MeV,",
                " (g,2n+2p+3a)  -  42.8  MeV  in (g,2n) reaction cross",
                " sections and hence in their sum sig (g,n-tot)."
              ]
            }
          ],
